other_tests.findings: Well-appearing patient with vital signs of 100.0 temperature, 68 heart rate, and blood pressure of 165/94. Focally tender to palpation at RLQ/suprapubic region, mildly distended abdomen. Negative Rovsing, obturator, psoas signs. Reducible umbilical hernia with 2-cm defect.

Dilated loops of small bowel measuring up to 4.8 cm. Air within the colon, but no significant air overlying the rectum. Surgical skin staples noted overlying the right lower quadrant/pelvis. Degenerative changes throughout the visualized spine.
1+ (<1 per 1000X FIELD): Polymorphonuclear leukocytes. No microorganisms seen.
